    "Problem Formalization": "We model the transverse displacement u(x,t) of a uniform vibrating string on x ∈ [0,L] and t ∈ [0,T] with fixed ends u(0,t)=0, u(L,t)=0. The governing PDE is the 1D wave equation u_tt = c² u_xx, where wave speed c > 0 is known. The initial conditions are given as measured data: u(x,0) = f(x) (displacement) and u_t(x,0) = g(x) (velocity). The measurements may not exactly satisfy the boundary conditions at the corners (f(0)=f(L)=0, g(0)=g(L)=0), leading to a compatibility mismatch.",
    "Physics Constraints": "The model must satisfy the wave equation u_tt = c² u_xx almost everywhere, the fixed-end boundary conditions u(0,t)=0, u(L,t)=0, and the two initial conditions u(x,0)=f(x) and u_t(x,0)=g(x). The ideal system conserves total mechanical energy E(t) = ½ ∫[0,L] ( (u_t)² + c² (u_x)² ) dx under these ideal conditions; this invariant will be monitored during validation.",
